@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="privacy-policy container mt-4 mb-5 text-black">
    <h1 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information in accordance with the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA).
    </p>

    <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
    <p>
        TraqBanking (“we”, “us”, “our”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information in accordance with the
        <strong>Protection of Personal Information Act, 4 of 2013 (POPIA)</strong>.
        By using our website or mobile application, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Information We Collect</h3>
    <h4>2.1 Information You Provide Directly</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Full name, surname, and identification number</li>
        <li>Contact details (email address, phone number, physical address)</li>
        <li>Login details (username, encrypted password)</li>
        <li>Banking or payment information for transactions</li>
        <li>Information submitted via forms or feedback</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>2.2 Information We Collect Automatically</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Device, browser, and operating system details</li>
        <li>IP address and general location</li>
        <li>Pages visited, actions taken, and time spent</li>
        <li>Cookies and similar tracking data</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>2.3 Information from Third Parties</h4>
    <p>
        We may receive verification data or updates from trusted third parties (e.g., banks or identity verification services).
    </p>

    <h3>3. Purpose of Processing Personal Information</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide and maintain user accounts</li>
        <li>Facilitate secure transactions</li>
        <li>Verify identities and comply with FICA</li>
        <li>Communicate about accounts and updates</li>
        <li>Improve products and services</li>
        <li>Prevent fraud and security breaches</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4. Lawful Basis for Processing</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Your consent</li>
        <li>Performance of a contract</li>
        <li>Compliance with legal requirements</li>
        <li>Legitimate business interests</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. How We Protect Your Information</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Data encryption in transit and at rest</li>
        <li>Secure authentication and access controls</li>
        <li>Regular audits and monitoring</li>
        <li>Restricted data access on a need-to-know basis</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>6. Sharing of Information</h3>
    <p>
        We do not sell or rent personal information. Data may be shared with:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Service providers who assist in operations</li>
        <li>Regulatory authorities as required by law</li>
        <li>Trusted business partners (only with consent)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7. Cross-Border Transfers</h3>
    <p>
        If personal information is transferred outside South Africa, we ensure adequate data protection standards equivalent to POPIA.
    </p>

    <h3>8. Data Retention</h3>
    <p>
        We retain your personal information only as long as necessary to fulfil the purpose for which it was collected or as required by law.
    </p>

    <h3>9. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
    <p>
        We use cookies to enhance your experience, analyse usage, and remember preferences. You may disable cookies in your browser settings, but some features may not function properly.
    </p>

    <h3>10. Your Rights Under POPIA</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Access and request a copy of your personal data</li>
        <li>Request correction or deletion of data</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent for processing</li>
        <li>Object to certain data uses</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="info-box mt-3">
        <strong>Information Regulator Contact Details:</strong><br>
        Website: <a href="https://www.justice.gov.za/inforeg/" target="_blank">https://www.justice.gov.za/inforeg/</a><br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:inforeg@justice.gov.za">inforeg@justice.gov.za</a><br>
        Tel: +27 (0)10 023 5200
    </div>

    <h3>11. Children’s Privacy</h3>
    <p>
        We do not knowingly collect information from anyone under 18 years old. If you believe a minor has shared their details, please contact us immediately.
    </p>

    <h3>12. Updates to This Policy</h3>
    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Updates will be published on our website with the latest effective date.
    </p>

    <h3>13. Contact Us</h3>
    <p>
        For questions or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, contact our Data Protection Officer:
    </p>
    <address>
        <strong>TraqBanking Data Protection Officer</strong><br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@traqbanking.co.za">privacy@traqbanking.co.za</a><br>
        Phone: +27 (0)31 123 4567<br>
        Address: 123 Main Road, Durban, South Africa
    </address>
</section>
